his year. He had heard the Soviets were seeking an American squad for some exhibition games, and suggested the <PERSON> Johns </PERSON> <PERSON> Hopkins </PERSON> team. The Soviet media publicized the game, and several newspapers ran stories that caught the spirit of good will. A front-page article in Tuesday's editions of the newspaper Sovietsky Sport carried the headline: `` When the score does n't count.
