<HEAD>City Covers Up Pornography Law's Loophole</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents</NOTE>
<DATELINE>EL PASO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Flustered </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> members closed a loophole in a pornography ordinance after topless dancers began smearing themselves with transparent grease to slip out of a requirement that they cover up. Before it was amended Tuesday, the ordinance specified what parts of dancers' bodies had to be covered but did n't say the covering had to be opaque. `` Some of the girls ... were covering their breasts with Vaseline or grease,'' said <PERSON> Brenda </PERSON> <PERSON> Nichols </PERSON>, assistant city attorney. There were reports that other dancers used see-through fabric and clear adhesive tape to skirt the ordinance. Tuesday's Council action banned all such clear coverings. The Council also amended the ordinance to make sure adult entertainment establishments are at least 1,000 feet from homes, schools, churches, parks or other adult businesses. The amendment went into effect immediately. Those who still want to see strippers can easily cross an international bridge to <LOCATION> Ciudad </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Juarez </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>, where nude dancing and prostitution are legal. <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Gibson </PERSON>, a lawyer who represents some of the adult businesses here, said <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> simply is trying to stamp out adult businesses in <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Paso </LOCATION>. `` If you comply with the first ordinance they pass, they change it to make sure no one can comply,'' he said. `` With the new definition of the type of covering, you might as well set up outside a swimming pool and charge admission to it.''
