 Indian representative <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Gonzales </PERSON> of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> told <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> that <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s remarks at <ORGANIZATION> Moscow </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> Tuesday were `` typical of American racism.'' <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> told the peace activists that each society must be able to choose its own course, without outside interference. He said long experience of Russians and other Soviets with Christianity is proof that they can understand themselves and their society without advice from others.
