<HEAD>Interest Rates On Treasury Bills Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Interest rates on 52-week <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> bills rose in Thursday's action to the highest level since before the October stock market crash. The <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> sold $ 8.8 billion of the bills at an average discount rate of 7.08 percent, up from 6.74 percent at the last auction on May 5. The rates were the highest since Sept. 30, when the one-year bills sold for 7.32 percent. The new discount rate understates the actual return to investors _ 7.59 percent with a $ 10,000 bill selling for $ 9,284.10.
