ed that the newspaper, which had its first profitable quarter at the end of 1987, would either show a profit or a marginal loss for all of 1988. <ORGANIZATION> Gannett </ORGANIZATION> owns and operates 90 daily newspapers, 35 non-dailies, 10 television stations, 16 radio stations, and the largest outdoor advertising operation in <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, according to a company news release.
