 hurricanes with winds over 74 mph. Tropical depressions can become tropical storms if their circulating winds reach 39 mph. Storms become hurricanes if those winds hit 74 mph. In 1987 there were three hurricanes and four tropical storms in the <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION>.
