exploring.'' `` There is probably not much Olmeca in <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>,'' he was quoted as saying. <ORGANIZATION> Pemex </ORGANIZATION>, meanwhile, reported that prices to Japanese clients for Isthmus and Maya crudes were held steady in May The price for Isthmus was $ 15.30 a barrel in May to <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>, the same as in April, and for Maya, $ 12.60 a barrel. `` This reflects the stability that prevails in the general level of prices in the international oil market,'' <ORGANIZATION> Pemex </ORGANIZATION> said in a statement. <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> has a contract with Japanese customers to supply 180,000 barrels of oil a day, the statement said. <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>'s prices vary according to geographical area. The oil company did not give the May prices for <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> and European customers. In April, the price of the Isthmus brand to <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> customers was $ 16 a barrel and $ 12.77 for the heavy type. <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> maintains an export platform of 1.36 million barrels a day.
