<FIRST>u f PM-WallStreetClosing     06-02 0114</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wall Street Closing,0124</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices suffered a mild setback today, giving up some of their recent gains as interest rates turned upward. Interest rates rose in the credit markets, reversing a sharp decline Tuesday and Wednesday. Analysts also noted an increase in British interest rates. That prompted many traders to sell stocks in order to cash in on the gains of the past two sessions, brokers said. The upswing in stock prices since the start of the week was met with considerable skepticism on Wall Street, given continued signs of upward pressure on commodity prices. Futures prices for commodities ranging from soybeans to gold moved up today.
</TEXT>
