<HEAD>Textile Giant Strengthens Its Takeover Defense</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST POINT, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> West </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Point-Pepperell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> announced steps to strengthen its `` poison pill'' takeover defense Thursday, a little more than a week after it revealed plans by <ORGANIZATION> Farley </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> to purchase up to 25 percent of its common stock. The Georgia-based textile company announced that its board had amended its share purchase rights plan, which allows existing stockholders to purchase additional shares at reduced prices in the event of a takeover bid. The plan is designed to make a hostile takeover more expensive. Previously, the plan was effective when a person or group acquired 20 percent or more of <LOCATION> Pepperell </LOCATION>'s common stock or announced a tender offer. Under the amendment, the threshold is 10 percent. <LOCATION> Pepperell </LOCATION> announced May 25 it had been notified of <PERSON> Farley </PERSON>'s filing with the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> for permission to purchase up to 25 percent of <LOCATION> Pepperell </LOCATION>'s approximately 32 million outstanding shares <PERSON> Farley </PERSON>, a conglomerate privately owned by <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Farley </PERSON>, includes in its holdings Fruit of the <ORGANIZATION> Loom </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, the underwear manufacturer. <PERSON> Pepperell </PERSON> recently became the nation's largest publicly owned textile company when it acquired <ORGANIZATION> J.P. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stevens </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> in a joint buyout with <ORGANIZATION> Odyssey </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. <LOCATION> Pepperell </LOC